Descriptive statistics

Source: vignettes/articles/descriptives.Rmd
descriptives.Rmd
library(ASQ3) # Load the package with the data

# Complementary packages
library(data.table)
library(skimr)

We will first calculate the statistics for the entire database without considering the underlying structure of the database.

descriptives <- skim(dataset)
#> Warning in sorted_count(x): Variable contains value(s) of "" that have been converted to "empty".

print(descriptives)

Despite the above results, we cannot ignore that there is more than one observation per subject, so it is necessary to consider each subject as the minimum unit of analysis. For this we will use the last observation for each subject.

descriptives_by_patient <- skim(
  data = dataset[, .SD[which.max(fecha_evaluacion)], keyby = paciente_id]
)
#> Warning in sorted_count(x): Variable contains value(s) of "" that have been converted to "empty".

print(descriptives_by_patient)
